description:
"The Savior Is Waiting" & "Turn Your Eyes Upon Jesus"
Words & Music: Ralph Carmichael
Words: Helen H. Lemmel, 1922

[THE SAVIOR IS WAITING TO ENTER YOUR HEART - LYRICS]

The Savior is waiting to enter your heart
Why don't you let Him come in?
There's nothing in this world to keep you apart
What is your answer to Him?

Chorus:
Time after time
He has waited before
And now He is waiting again
To see if you're willing
To open the door
Oh, how He wants to come in.

If you'll take one step
Toward the Savior, my friend,
You'll find His arms open wide.
Receive Him, and all of your darkness will end
Within your heart He'll abide.

Chorus:
Time after time
He has waited before
And now He is waiting again
To see if you're willing
To open the door
Oh, how He wants to, please, won't you let Him,
Oh, how He wants to come in.

[TURN YOUR EYES UPON JESUS - LYRICS]

Turn your eyes upon Jesus
Look full in His wonderful face
And the things of Earth will grow strangely dim
In the light of His glory and grace
In the light of His glory and grace

"The Present Truth's Songs of Worship" offers a collection of hymns and spiritual songs that uplift Jesus Christ and encourage your heart.

ABOUT THE SPEAKER
Stephen D. Lewis is a man who understands what it means to be saved by grace. That understanding is clearly seen in his passion for Christ and his love for people. 

Lewis is the featured speaker of the television and radio program, The Present Truth, which is nationally broadcast on several stations. His interest and aim is on winning and reviving personal commitments to a Saviour, Jesus, the Christ, "so that we can go home!”
